
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [add] slot to append nodes. It retrieves nodes from the [.arguments] node using [get-nodes] for both "order" and "direction" and adds them to the current node's children. The [add] slot is used to append the retrieved nodes to the specified destination.
add:x:./*/data.read
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/order
   get-nodes:x:@.arguments/*/direction
